<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="3" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d3">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.1012 Anti-War/69</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Weddell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 228</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-23">March 23, 1934</date>.<lb/>[Received April
                                2.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to my despatch No. 207 of
                            March 13, enclosing a certified copy of the Anti-War Treaty initiated by
                            the Argentine Minister for Foreign Affairs, I have the honor to enclose
                            herewith a copy and translation of a note I received today from the
                                Minister<note n="4" xml:id="d3fn4">Not printed.</note> asking me to
                            obtain from my Government as soon as possible the authorization to sign
                            the document of adhesion to the Anti-War Treaty at a meeting which will
                            take place at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs in the near future, at the
                            same time as the signature of adhesion of several other nations.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alexander W.
                            Weddell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>